modules.description: Parses a string into a structured query representation, handling valid query formats and returning None for invalid inputs. Converts structured queries back into string form for output or transmission. Operates on a custom type representing parsed query components, such as filters and parameters. Used to process user input from APIs or configuration files into a usable format.

Provides functions to parse, compare, and increment semantic version numbers. Works with strings and a custom version type representing major, minor, and patch components. Enables version control in package management and dependency resolution workflows.

Parses and serializes structured query representations, supporting conversion between string inputs and internal data formats. Operates on a custom type that encapsulates query elements like filters and parameters. Allows for safe handling of user-provided queries by validating and transforming them. Can process API inputs, configuration files, or serialized data, ensuring consistent and reliable query manipulation.
